  "email": "Subject: Junior bioinformatics — UCSD BioE/Math-CS grad, software engineering background\n\nDear Dr. Yip,\n\nI'm a UC San Diego senior finishing B.S. degrees in Bioengineering: Biotechnology and Mathematics–Computer Science this September, writing about bioinformatics positions in the Shared Resource and the Center for Data Science and AI.\n\nI'm a software engineer who came to biology through my degree rather than the other way around. I've shipped two applications to the App Store, maintain CI/CD producing signed releases, and run a containerized self-hosted Linux stack. On the biology side: Bioinformatic Algorithms and Biological Databases coursework, local alignment implemented from scratch, and an RNA sequence-and-structure scoring tool now packaged as an installable, tested, containerized Nextflow workflow: [GitHub link].\n\nWould you have time for a short conversation about what the core needs?\n\nBest regards,\nSuraj Laddagiri\nportfolio.sladdagiri.org",
