  "email": "Subject: Computational neuroscience — UCSD Math-CS/BioE grad\n\nDear Dr. Sharpee,\n\nI'm a UC San Diego senior finishing B.S. degrees in Mathematics–Computer Science and Bioengineering: Biotechnology this September, writing to ask about computational positions in the lab.\n\nMy preparation is Machine Learning, NLP, Computer Vision, Linear Algebra and Numerical Analysis, plus the Stanford/DeepLearning.AI machine learning certification. For a course project I trained 535 transformer-based classifiers and analyzed where they systematically failed — class imbalance producing a 0.91/0.64 recall gap between the two classes — which taught me more than the accuracy number did.\n\nTo engage with the lab's own lineage I implemented ICA from scratch and applied it to source separation in public EEG data, comparing against a reference implementation: [GitHub link].\n\nWould you have 20 minutes?\n\nBest regards,\nSuraj Laddagiri\nportfolio.sladdagiri.org",
